CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 12, 1969, pg. 16, reads: "Minster and Teacher Marry in Pittsburgh - Minster and Bride - The Rev. Joseph D. Martin Jr. and his bride, the former Deborah M. Alexander, cut the first slice of their wedding cake at their recent reception in Sixth Mt. Zion Church, Pittsburgh. The new bride, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Clarence Alexander of New Castle, is a schoolteacher in Butler. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom Rev. Joseph D. Martin Jr., and bride Deborah M. Alexander Martin posed behind three tiered wedding cake, possibly in Sixth Mt. Zion Baptist Church decorated with floral wreaths shaped as double wedding rings
